cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper discusses the success of Highway and Residual networks in training feedforward networks with dozens to hundreds of layers using simple gradient descent. This topic is closely related to machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses on the architecture of these networks rather than their specific applications, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.CV and cs.NE.
